This paper deals with sentiment classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a variational approach and latent variables suggests that this paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of target-opinion word pairs and dependency parsers suggests that this paper may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV), which often involve similar techniques for text and image analysis.
